definitions.definition: To thwart or stump ; to cause to fail or to leave hopelessly puzzled , confused , or stuck .
examples: They had lost the key, and the lock stymied the first three locksmiths they called.
If writing dates has you stymied at times, it is probably for one of two reasons.

definitions.definition: To bring into the position of, or impede by, a stymie.
